he concept of survival to rethink border deaths beyond the structures and processes that produce the murderous border and constitute the focus of critical migration studies. It demonstrates how the process of survival transforms people and societies. Survival is productive, Horsti argues, shifting the focus in migration studies from apparatuses of control to emphasize the agency and subjectivity of refugees.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEritreanszEuropexSocial conditionsy21st century. 0aShipwreckszMediterranean SeaxHistoryy21st century. 4aGEOGRAPHY. 4aSOCIOLOGY & SOCIAL SCIENCE. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  amigrant deaths, European border, refugee crisis, Eritrean refugees, Lampedusa disaster, Europe’s migration policies, strage di Lampedusa, Lampedusa migrant shipwreck, migration and borders.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311075183308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023 Englishz978311131926108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023z9783111318806oZDB-23-DSL40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501771385?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501771385423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501771385/original  a978-3-11-075183-3  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131926-1  EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZ